Step 14 - Have the user enter the next number, i.e. the radius, which will be used
to calculate the area and the circumference.
// create my second input dialog box so the user can enter the radius
String numPiAndCircumfrance = JOptionPane.showInputDialog("Now, enter the
radius of your circle");
radiusEntered = Integer.parseInt(numPiAndCircumfrance)
Step 15 - Calculate the area using the radius entered
area = PI*radiusEntered;
circumference = 2*PI*radiusEntered;
Step 16 - Display the area and circumference calculated to the user using a
message dialog box
JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "area = " + area + "\ncircumferance = " +
circumference );
Step 17 - Make sure the public static void main is within the closing brace of the
class
} // this is the closing brace of the method calcGuiApp()
public static void main(String[] args) {
} // this is the closing brace for public static void main
} // this is the closing brace of the class!
